{"id":"project-LICHEN-oy70","title":"aprs_is.rs: dead code in login response parsing","description":"File: rust/lichen-gateway/src/aprs_is.rs
Lines: 282-286

The else-if branch at line 282 is unreachable dead code. The condition checks for 'logresp' AND 'unverified', but since 'unverified' contains the substring 'verified', the first branch (line 272) will always match first.

Current code:
```rust
if response.contains("logresp") && response.contains("verified") {
    // This branch handles BOTH verified AND unverified
    self.verification = if response.contains("unverified") {
        Some(AprsVerification::Unverified)
    } else {
        Some(AprsVerification::Verified)
    };
    Ok(())
} else if response.contains("logresp") && response.contains("unverified") {
    // DEAD CODE: unreachable because 'unverified' contains 'verified'
    self.verification = Some(AprsVerification::Unverified);
    Ok(())
} else {
    Err(AprsError::LoginFailed(response))
}
```

Impact: None - the logic is correct, but the dead code is confusing. The first branch correctly handles both cases via the inner check.

Fix: Remove the unreachable else-if branch:
```rust
if response.contains("logresp") && response.contains("verified") {
    self.callsign = callsign.to_string();
    self.verification = if response.contains("unverified") {
        Some(AprsVerification::Unverified)
    } else {
        Some(AprsVerification::Verified)
    };
    Ok(())
} else {
    Err(AprsError::LoginFailed(response))
}
```

